raw_data.description: Charlotte Mecklenburg Library is the library system serving Mecklenburg County, NC with 20 locations and a digital online site. Our mission is to improve lives and build a stronger community. We create a community of readers and empower individuals.
raw_data.typical_time_spent: People typically spend up to 1.5 hours here

reviews_data.review_text: I was there conducting an interview and I have never been so harassed. That by far is the loudest library I’ve ever attended. The attendant had no consideration of the business I was conducting and she kept coming to my area making comments about hearing me when in fact there was no way she heard me due to the loudness in that library. I will be escalating this matter. As a tax payer of Mecklenburg County I am highly offended. She turned her badge so I couldn’t see her name. I only have 1 star because 0 wasn’t an option.
It's great having a library close by!

Absolutely sick and tired of people being on their phones while in a quiet room that has signs clearly posted, "please take phone calls outside."  I'm also sick and tired of talking to staff about it and getting no results, they would much rather just sit on their computers at the front desk.  Not a quiet place to study or do work!

It's a nice library and great location. The issue is the quiet areas are NOT QUIET. The librarians and security guard do not say anything to the people whose cell phones are going off and who are talking at regular conversational tones rather than whispering or being silent.
The staff is ever so helpful!!

My visit to the library was awesome since the employees helped me so much. It was almost closing time on Saturday but they went out of their way to help me understand the system since I mentioned I was new to the country. They offered every resource the library has to offer for students and explained everything in an informative way. They were patient and each came forward to help with books be digital or paperback and offered a lot of valuable information. Thank you .
Tiny library with dirty bathrooms. When a child cries it echos throughout. Wish it was bigger.
ok location but the library is hidden from rivergate. I don't like the entry setup from the back its supposed to be up front.
fun good scenery would escape to go there and chill if i could
The Charlotte libraries are better than the Rock Hill libraries
Good choice. Plenty of community resources along with the hands on internet up to date computers.  Very friendly staff and convenience for library access to videos.  I like it there.  Nice place😗

I came in today needing to print some papers for an interview. I was having trouble doing it and Kelly happily helped me out to make sure I got everything printed correctly/in a timely manner. Such kind people here, highly recommend this library to everyone!
such a cute library- known it for about 10 years (when I was in middle school) and now as an adult of 28. Quiet, clean, safe
We love Steele Creek library! The staff are always so kind. The children’s programming is excellent.
This library is quaint with extraordinarily friendly workers. We really enjoy coming to this location because of its proximity. It’s clean, quiet and pleasant.
Walk in, and Gabriel was the nicest, most pleasant person I've met all morning. He got my new library card setup and showed me where the computer was.

Well, I certainly do love libraries and books (yes, we got our library cards just shortly after locating to Charlotte), and indeed the librarians we encountered here, certainly appear to love their work! Phenomenal location and wonderful librarians, it's a win-win here at Charlotte Mecklenburg Library - Steele Creek-thanks so much for all you do, you are a blessing!
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thank you for the review and thanks for being part of the CML family!

reviews_data.review_text: They have a quiet area with tables that's perfect for work, and the Wi-Fi is fast. It's a great spot for getting things done or diving into a good book.
This is a wonderful library. It has a very diverse collection and the children's area is welcoming. It also has an outside garden area. My grandson loves visiting.
Very nice building, quiet, especially since school is out.
I visit usually during my lunch to work on my business in a quite space without distractions. The staff is very welcoming and helpful when a need arise.
One of the best library with beautiful ambience . I love the park where you can sit and enjoy reading …

Very patient staff when I'm learning how to use their printer. They have a lot of selections of books. Clean environment. Parking is very spacious. I love their outdoor vines. Makes it feel like a fairytale.

We love this library! There is a lady there that went above and beyond to help so many kids tonight with book suggestions and a scavenger hunt. She helped my son find 3 great books that he can’t wait to read!

Absolutely the BEST Library I have ever been in... The Staff is very very Cordial and go the Extra Mile to help you with anything you need... I travel all the way from South Carolina just to go here🍎❤🍎
reviews_data.owner_answer: Wow, Renee! Thank you so much for your kind review. We are honored you make the trip for us. We look forward to seeing you again!

reviews_data.review_text: This branch is fantastic! The librarians are always ready to help.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thanks, Zip! We appreciate your review and look forward to seeing you again soon!

reviews_data.review_text:
Wonderfully helpful staff.
Facility and restrooms very clean.
(Very important these days)
Convenient hours to serve the public.

Small but easy to access and great selection. It is part of a 20 branch library system so you will be able to get anything within the system. They also offer patrons access to popular audio book/ebook collections on Libby, hoopla, overdrive and others.

Stumble into something interesting if I stop by. Good curation by librarians. Find things that don’t come up on Amazon. Was looking for a more comfy reading area that some other libraries offer. Self checkout is cool.

I don't often go to the library anymore because I like to take advantage of of their e-books online.

The biggest benefit that brings me into the library is free printing. I don't have a printer and I don't ever plan to have a printer, so every once in a while when I need to print something, it's really convenient to be able to come here to do it.

They have an app you can use to upload your document and print it which is really convenient so you don't have to email it to yourself. They also used this during the pandemic when they weren't letting people inside.

If you're like me and don't want a printer, check out your local library!

I recently moved to the area from Georgia and I must say what I just experienced at this location was nothing short of AMAZING!!! I called prior to driving over and spoke with Angela whom gave me all the information I needed and more. When I arrived I encountered Michelle is explained everything to me that I needed and made my time here short and I was able to complete everything I needed!!! Thank you ladies for allowing me to have an AMAZING welcome to Charlotte!!! I definitely will be back!!!
Quiet but you can walk in and it's so simple.  Of course the staff are very helpful !!

I was helped by Sara and Whitney.  This was the greatest experience. Whitney was super friendly while Sara patiently waited on my copies. They also followed the Covid 19 policies and procedures, which made me feel comfortable! I haven't visited a library in over 20 years. I am an Army Vet and always recognize kindness and respect. Please please please show these lovely ladies some recognition! Thanks ladies! You make times like this seem not so bad... with what we're experiencing now!

I enjoy coming to this library. I bring my daughter here for the storytime. The staff here is always friendly and helpful. The librarians who conduct baby storytime are AMAZING! I recommend bringing your little ones here.
Super staff
The Liberian Sarah,  she's so caring
My favorite branch! Staff is always friendly and helpful
Quiet environment. There is a Silent Study Room!

This Charlotte library is in a charming building with lots of natural light and has a wide variety of books.  Their kids section is comprehensive, but not as big as some of the other Charlotte libraries. They have an incredible collection of stuffed animals that always gets the kids attention. They offer a lot of programs for the kids, always have book sales, and have many resources for adults.  I recommend this library!
Loud place
Nice open space with kind, helpful staff. Definitely kid friendly as well
Friendly staff always ready to help, new books always there, quick arrival time if books are put on hold, a great book sale, and the clean grounds make this the best library I have ever been to.
One of the best libraries in the area
Friendly employees, rest room A+,  quiet surrounding,
Very nice and stocked library...
Great staff!  Consistently helpful to my family!  Thank you!
I truly enjoy our local Library (Steel Creek) There many resources for good research there. Very thankful for that and very nice people. Thanks.

Medium sized library.
Kids area:
Two touch screen kids computers
Six regular computers
Small DVD collection
Large book selection
Bean bags around for lounging
Play area with a sectional type seating area with big cushions, a table with chairs and, puzzles.
Rug with wooden play cube and small bins of toys.
BEAUTIFUL  garden area with bin with outside toys.
Staff was nice
Story time (toddler)
Stories are short (great for busy minds)
Music is fun (lots of movement)
Bubbles at end are nice

Negatives
Story teller said "if at any time someone is unhappy with the story, take them out and bring them back in when they're done". I hate this because it usually embarrasses a parent. One person had to leave because of this. I don't think it's fair. Let the babies cry if they need to!
Sign outside door telling others story time was full. We had plenty of room outside. There is no need to turn anyone away. Ever.

I wish I could say my first experience at this branch was great , however it was not . Mamas please note that if you are even 5 minutes late to attend one of their story time activities they will not let you in . Ms Joe ( runs this like the military) and  had no grace in allowing me to go in with my 7 mo old despite it being our 1 st time and driving 25 min to get there. Come on ya'll I was pretty bummed and disappointed being that this was my daughters first time ever attending story time . Ms Joe needs to be a bit more gracious and understanding . However I will try again next time and hopefully  the rest of the staff is more friendly and understanding.
Small library, but well stocked and tended by very helpful staff.
Polite staff and clean organized small space.
